-- Thailand Stocks: Khon Kaen, Malee, Thai Union, Tipco Foods
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-03-28T09:52:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/bangkok-bank-chow-steel-ptt-exploration-thai-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  fell 0.3 percent to 1,204.01, trimming this
year’s rally to 17 percent. The gauge is heading for the biggest
quarterly gain since the three months ended September 2010.  Khon Kaen Sugar Industry Pcl (KSL)  , a sugar producer,
dropped 1.4 percent to 14.30 baht, the biggest loss since March
13. Raw-sugar futures for May delivery fell 1.9 percent to 24.3
cents a pound on ICE Futures U.S. in  New York  yesterday.  Malee Sampran Pcl (MALEE)  , a fruit-juice producer,
jumped 19 percent to 47.25 baht, the highest close since April
1994. Investors bought Malee’s shares on speculation the company
may be a takeover target amid improving profits, Jitra
Amornthum, an analyst at Finansia Syrus Securities, said by
phone today. Paitoon Eiamsirikulmit, Malee’s head of corporate
affairs, declined to comment. Paitoon is unaware of the reason
for the stock’s gain, he said by phone today.  Thai Union Frozen Products Pcl (TUF)  , the nation’s
largest seafood exporter, gained 1.1 percent to 70.25 baht. Thai
Union has invested 3.3 billion baht ($107 million) in the past
year to add more machinery ahead of wage increases, Wai Yat Paco Lee, the company’s financial controller, said in a meeting with
investors yesterday. Thai Union also plans to raise product
prices to maintain profit margins, Lee said.  Tipco Foods Pcl (TIPCO)  , a producer of canned pineapple
and fruit juice, jumped 6 percent to 6.20 baht, the highest
close since January 2008. Exports of canned pineapple climbed
more than previously estimated in the first quarter on demand
from the U.S. and  Europe , Nitima Aungatichart, Tipco’s head of
 investor relations , said by phone from Bangkok today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
